# 4ï¸âƒ£ Client Project â€“ Mini Dashboard

## ğŸ“Š Project: Student Performance Visualization Dashboard

In this project, I created multiple visualizations to understand relationships between student marks and study hours.

---

# ğŸ’» WEEK 4 PYTHON SCRIPT

Save as: `week4_visualization.py`

```python
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Create sample dataset
data = {
    "Student": ["A", "B", "C", "D", "E"],
    "Study_Hours": [2, 4, 6, 3, 5],
    "Marks": [50, 65, 85, 60, 75]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# -----------------------------
# 1. Line Plot
plt.figure()
plt.plot(df["Student"], df["Marks"])
plt.title("Student Marks Line Chart")
plt.xlabel("Student")
plt.ylabel("Marks")
plt.show()

# -----------------------------
# 2. Bar Plot
plt.figure()
plt.bar(df["Student"], df["Marks"])
plt.title("Marks Bar Chart")
plt.xlabel("Student")
plt.ylabel("Marks")
plt.show()

# -----------------------------
# 3. Histogram
plt.figure()
plt.hist(df["Marks"], bins=5)
plt.title("Marks Distribution")
plt.xlabel("Marks")
plt.ylabel("Frequency")
plt.show()

# -----------------------------
# 4. Scatter Plot
plt.figure()
plt.scatter(df["Study_Hours"], df["Marks"])
plt.title("Study Hours vs Marks")
plt.xlabel("Study Hours")
plt.ylabel("Marks")
plt.show()

# -----------------------------
# 5. Heatmap
plt.figure()
corr = df[["Study_Hours", "Marks"]].corr()
sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True)
plt.title("Correlation Heatmap")
plt.show()
```

---

# 5ï¸âƒ£ Learning Outcome

By completing Week 4:

* I understood the importance of data visualization.
* I created different types of charts using Matplotlib.
* I used Seaborn for advanced visualizations.
* I analyzed relationships between dataset features.
* I created a mini dashboard combining multiple plots.





